 tellus penatibus turpis auctor maecenas. ','trash','open','open','','activity__trashed','','','2016-06-23 16:49:10','2016-06-23 16:49:10','',0,'http://localhost/shinetheme/Travel/travel-code/?post_type=st_activity&#038;p=1034',0,'st_activity','',1),(6022,3,'2016-06-23 17:15:50','2016-06-23 17:15:50','The Museo Rafael Coronel located in the former San Francisco Convent, displays an interesting collection of Mexican folk art, based in the main exhibit called \"The Face of Mexico\" which consists of more than five thousand Mexican masks.  This museum also exhibits a part of the colorful collection of puppets from the Rosette Aranda Company, an interesting exhibition of pre-Columbian pots and vases, various drawings, sketches and architectural projects of Diego Rivera’s, terracotta figurines from colonial Mexico, and other pieces from varying pre-Hispanic, colonial and contemporary times.\r\n\r\nRafael Coronel was born in 1931 in the city of Zacatecas, and abandoned a career in architecture to devote himself entirely to painting. He attended the National School of Plastic Arts of  UNAM. In 1944 he painted his first self-portrait, and in 1952 he received the Arts Award from the National Institute of Mexican Youth.\r\nHe is considered to be one of the leading definitive representatives of new Mexican expressionism.  In 1978, along with his brother Pedro Coronel, he was declared “Hijo Predilecto” meaning  “Favorite Son”  by the State Government and the Autonomous University of Zacatecas.\r\nIn 1990, he gave his collection of Mexican Art to create the Museo Rafael Coronel.\r\n','Visit the Rafael Coronel museum','The Museo Rafael Coronel located in the former San Francisco Convent, displays an interesting collection of Mexican folk art, based in the main exhibit called \"The Face of Mexico\" which consists of more than five thousand Mexican masks.  This museum also exhibits a part of the colorful collection of puppets from the Rosette Aranda Company, an interesting exhibition of pre-Columbian pots and vases, various drawings, sketches and architectural projects of Diego Rivera’s, terracotta figurines from colonial Mexico, and other pieces from varying pre-Hispanic, colonial and contemporary times.\r\n\r\nRafael Coronel was born in 1931 in the city of Zacatecas, and abandoned a career in architecture to devote himself entirely to painting. He attended the National School of Plastic Arts of  UNAM. In 1944 he painted his first self-portrait, and in 1952 he received the Arts Award from the National Institute of Mexican Youth.\r\nHe is considered to be one of the leading definitive representatives of new Mexican expressionism.  In 1978, along with his brother Pedro Coronel, he was declared “Hijo Predilecto” meaning  “Favorite Son”  by the State Government and the Autonomous University of Zacatecas.\r\nIn 1990, he gave his collection of Mexican Art to create the Museo Rafael Coronel.\r\n','trash','open','closed','','visit-the-rafael-coronel-museum__trashed','','','2016-07-01 12:52:05','2016-07-01 12:52:05','',0,'http://hiddentreasures.ingsoft.info/demo1/?post_type=st_activity&#038;p=6022',0,'st_activity','',0),(6023,3,'2016-06-23 17:40:17','2016-06-23 17:40:17','','rafael_coronel_museum','','inherit','open','closed','','rafael_coronel_museum','','','2016-06-23 17:40:17','2016-06-23 17:40:17','',6022,'http://hiddentreasures.ingsoft.info/demo1/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/rafael_coronel_museum.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1564,1,'2015-01-10 09:25:32','2015-01-10 09:25:32','Jerez is a town and municipality in the Mexican state of Zacatecas. To distinguish the two, the town, is officially called Jerez de Francisco García Salinas to honor an 18th-century reformer. The town of Jerez is the local government of 128 other communities, a rural area noted for its production of fruit trees and dairy. The town was named a Pueblo Mágico to attract tourism, as it lies close the state capital of Zacatecas and offers handcrafts, traditional food and architecture.','Visit Jeréz: Magical Town','Jerez is a town and municipality in the Mexican state of Zacatecas. To distinguish the two, the town, is officially called Jerez de Francisco García Salinas to honor an 18th-century reformer. The town of Jerez is the local government of 128 other communities, a rural area noted for its production of fruit trees and dairy. The town was named a Pueblo Mágico to attract tourism, as it lies close the state capital of Zacatecas and offers handcrafts, traditional food and architecture.','trash','open','closed','','a-walk-into-the-old-little-town__trashed','','','2016-07-01 12:52:08','2016-07-01 12:52:08','',0,'http://traveler.shinethemedev.com/wordpress/?post_type=st_activity&#038;p=1564',0,'st_activity','',1),(6021,3,'2016-06-23 17:10:11','2016-06-23 17:10:11','[vc_row row_fullwidth=\"yes\" css=\".vc_custom_1436433720935{margin-bottom: 100px !important;}\" el_class=\"st_gmap\"][vc_column css=\".vc_custom_1436411456565{padding-right: 0px !important;padding-left: 0px !important;}\"][st_list_map title=\"Find Your Perfect Activity\" st_list_location=\"1517\" st_type=\"st_activity\" number=\"12\" zoom=\"11\" height=\"500\" style_map=\"normal\" range_km=\"on\" max_range_km=\"20\" range_km_col=\"6\"][st_list_map_field_activity placeholder=\"Where are you planning to travel?\" st_select_field=\"address\" is_required=\"on\" st_col=\"col-md-6\" st_title=\"City or Destination\"][st_list_map_field_activity placeholder=\"mm.yyyy\" st_select_field=\"check_in\" st_col=\"col-md-3\" st_title=\"When\"][/st_list_map][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row parallax=\"content-moving\" row_fullwidth=\"yes\" parallax_class=\"yes\" css=\".vc_custom_1452159955627{padding-top: 60px !important;padding-bottom: 60px !important;background-image: url(http://localhost/hidden-treasures/tesoito//wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Hidden-Treasures.png) !important;}\"][vc_column][st_last_minute_deal st_post_type=\"st_activity\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_145215964