rro de la Bufa is the Cable Car Terminal of Zacatecas, which connects the Cerro de la Bufa with the Cerro del Grillo and the Mina \"El Edén\".\r\nIn addition to the hill’s own appeal, you can tour a number of attractions located here: the Plaza de la Revolucion Mexicana,  the Santuario del Patrocinio, the Toma de Zacatecas Museum, the Meteorological Observatory and the Mausoleum of Illustrious Men.\r\n\r\nIt is recommended to use comfortable walking shoes, a hat and sunscreen on hot days, and if possible binoculars which are great to have aside from the coin-operated binoculars that are found.','Climb the amazing hill of La Bufa','','trash','open','closed','','climb-the-amazing-hill-of-la-bufa__trashed','','','2016-07-01 12:52:04','2016-07-01 12:52:04','',0,'http://hiddentreasures.ingsoft.info/demo1/?post_type=st_activity&#038;p=6024',0,'st_activity','',0),(6042,3,'2016-06-27 17:25:32','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2016-06-27 17:25:32','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost/hidden-treasures/tesorito/?p=6042',0,'post','',0),(5944,2,'2016-06-17 16:10:35','2016-06-17 16:10:35','','jeres','','inherit','open','closed','','jeres','','','2016-06-17 16:10:35','2016-06-17 16:10:35','',1564,'http://hiddentreasures.ingsoft.info/demo1/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/jeres.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(5946,3,'2016-06-17 17:14:12','2016-06-17 17:14:12','[vc_row row_fullwidth=\"yes\" css=\".vc_custom_1436433720935{margin-bottom: 100px !important;}\" el_class=\"st_gmap\"][vc_column css=\".vc_custom_1436411456565{padding-right: 0px !important;padding-left: 0px !important;}\"][st_list_map title=\"Find Your Perfect Activity\" st_list_location=\"287\" st_type=\"st_activity\" number=\"12\" zoom=\"13\" height=\"500\" style_map=\"normal\" range_km=\"on\" max_range_km=\"20\" range_km_col=\"6\"][st_list_map_field_activity placeholder=\"Where are you planning to travel?\" st_select_field=\"address\" is_required=\"on\" st_col=\"col-m