f the Diocese of Zacatecas. Located in the historic city center, declared a World Heritage Site by Unesco. The main facade of the premises is known as one of the most outstanding examples of Baroque art in Mexico.','Catedral: Zacatecas','The Cathedral of Our Lady of the Assumption of Zacatecas, dedicated to Our Lady of the Assumption, is the head temple of the Diocese of Zacatecas. Located in the historic city center, declared a World Heritage Site by Unesco. The main facade of the premises is known as one of the most outstanding examples of Baroque art in Mexico.','inherit','closed','closed','','5985-autosave-v1','','','2016-06-23 15:41:38','2016-06-23 15:41:38','',5985,'http://hiddentreasures.ingsoft.info/demo1/?p=6015',0,'revision','',0),(6016,3,'2016-06-23 15:47:29','2016-06-23 15:47:29','Sombrerete is a town and municipality located in the northwest of the Mexican state of Zacatecas, bordering the state of Durango. It was founded as a mining center and this activity remains important to this day, along with agriculture and ranching.','Visit Sombrerete: Magical Town','Sombrerete is a town and municipality located in the northwest of the Mexican state of Zacatecas, bordering the state of Durango. It was founded as a mining center and this activity remains important to this day, along with agriculture and ranching.','inherit','closed','closed','','5977-autosave-v1','','','2016-06-23 15:47:29','2016-06-23 15:47:29','',5977,'http://hiddentreasures.ingsoft.info/demo1/?p=6016',0,'revision','',0),(6032,3,'2016-06-23 18:07:50','2016-06-23 18:07:50','La Quemada is a Mesoamerican archeological site, also known (according to different versions) as Chicomóztoc.[1][2] It is located in the Villanueva Municipality, in the state of Zacatecas, about 56 km south of the city of Zacatecas on Federal Highway 54 Zacatecas–Guadalajara, in Mexico.','Explore the archaeological site of La Quemada','La Quemada is a Mesoamerican archeological site, also known (according to different versions) as Chicomóztoc.[1][2] It is located in the Villanueva Municipality, in the state of Zacatecas, about 56 km south of the city of Zacatecas on Federal Highway 54 Zacatecas–Guadalajara, in Mexico.','trash','open','closed','','explore-the-archaeological-site-of-la-quemada__trashed','','','2016-07-01 12:52:03','2016-07-01 12:52:03','',0,'http://hiddentreasures.ingsoft.info/demo1/?post_type=st_activity&#038;p=6032',0,'st_activity','',0),(6033,2,'2016-06-23 18:07:22','2016-06-23 18:07:22','The Sierra de Organos (Organs Mountain Range) rises proudly from the surrounding ground, a mountainous chain of rock that stands out in unique shapes from the flat-lying landscape around it. Over the centuries, wind erosion has molded curious shapes and natural sculptures that resemble the pipes of an ancient church organ; people have given the different rocks names such as: monks, apache faces, whale, eagle, snake head, and so on. The rocks that, by popular accounts, resemble cathedrals, towers, castles and even monks, on average measure 200 feet in height, the tallest of them towering a colossal 265 feet. This mountain range, which belongs to the Western Sierra Madre, has been the set for several Mexican and international films, such as Navarone Canyons (starring Anthony Queen and Gregory Peck), and El Cavernicola, starring former Beatle, Ringo Starr.','Sombrerete','','trash','open','closed','','sombrerete__trashed','','','2016-07-01 14:30:14','2016-07-01 14:30:14','',0,'http://hiddentreasures.ingsoft.info/demo1/?post_type=location&#038;p=6033',0,'location','',0),(6034,3,'2016-06-23 18:05:46','2016-06-23 18:05:46','','La_Quemada,_Villanueva','','inherit','open','closed','','la_quemada_villanueva','','','2016-06-23 18:05:46','2016-06-23 18:05:46','',6032,'http://hiddentreasures.ingsoft.info/demo1/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/La_Quemada_Villanueva.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(6018,3,'2016-06-23 15:50:34','2016-06-23 15:50:34','','Take the tour through Mina El Edén','','inherit'